    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">1. Using Unauthorized Agents</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Only licensed agents can submit CBI applications. Working with unlicensed "facilitators" results in
            rejected applications and potential fraud. Verify agent authorization on the CIU website. Licensed
            agents have direct CIU relationships and understand current processing requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">2. Incomplete Source of Funds Documentation</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            The most common cause of delays. You must clearly document how you earned/accumulated the investment
            funds. Employment contracts, business ownership records, sale agreements, inheritance documents—all
            must create a clear trail. "I have the money" isn't sufficient; you must prove legitimate origin.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">3. Outdated Police Clearances</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Police clearances must be issued within 6 months of application. If you've lived in multiple countries
            in the past 10 years, you need clearances from each. Processing times vary—some countries take months.
            Start this process immediately when beginning your application.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">4. Skipping Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            Health insurance is required for application submission. Beyond compliance, anyone visiting Antigua
            needs evacuation coverage—Mount St. John's handles emergencies but complex cases require transfer
            to Miami or Puerto Rico. Budget $1,500-$5,000/year for comprehensive coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800">5. Forgetting the 5-Day Residency Requirement</h4>
          <p class="text-red-900 text-sm mt-1">
            While minimal, Antigua requires 5 days of physical presence within the first 5 years of citizenship.
            Failure to comply before passport renewal can create complications. Plan a vacation to fulfill this
            requirement—it's easy to overlook in the excitement of obtaining citizenship.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

